   Ad Notes. . . .
                                                                                                       

   AMTRAK: Amtrak will allow advertising on its ticket
jackets under an agreement reached with Devon Direct
Marketing &amp; Advertising, Malvern, Pa. With an annual
ridership of about 21 million, the rail carrier will offer
six million ticket jackets for advertising. Most major
airlines carry such ads.
                                                                                                       

   GERBER ACCOUNT: Gerber Products, Fremont, Mich., retained
TBWA Advertising, New York, to handle the launch of its new
Gerber Graduates food line for preschool children. Billings
haven't been determined, but the account eventually could be
valued at as much as $10 million. The Chicago office of J.
Walter Thompson, a WPP Group unit, continues to handle
Gerber's core baby-food business.
